headline: The Score: UnitedHealth, Intel, Walmart and More Stocks That Defined the Week
summary: Two Intel rivals are eyeing deals that would break the storied chipmaker in two.  Broadcom  has been closely examining Intel’s chip-design and marketing business, The Wall Street Journal reported on Feb. 15, while  Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing  has studied controlling some or all of Intel’s chip plants.  Broadcom and TSMC aren’t working together, and the talks are preliminary and largely informal.
